  "name": "Nagaraja COU1 — Non-cannulated pedicle screw compression-bending credibility assessment",
  "description": "V&V 40 credibility assessment for FEA prediction of ASTM F1717 static compression-bending performance of a non-cannulated 7.5 mm pedicle screw construct. COU1 is the validation activity itself — the FEA model ensemble (FDA, Ansys, DePuy Synthes) is compared against N=11 experimental constructs across two laboratories. All 13 V&V 40 factors assessed; one factor (Test conditions) below required level due to single test condition. A UQ campaign was conducted internally and sensitivity rankings are discussed in the validation report narrative; parameter influence on construct stiffness and yield force was evaluated via one-at-a-time perturbation of titanium alloy elastic modulus, cortical bone modulus, and friction coefficient. Structured sensitivity analysis metadata is captured in the supporting technical report (TR-NAG-2024-SA-01) referenced in the wasDerivedFrom provenance chain.",
